China’s Stocks Erase Gains, Head for Biggest Monthly Retreat Since June

-- B y   R i c h a r d   F r o s t
-- 
2011-05-31T03:22:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/china-s-stocks-erase-gains-head-for-biggest-monthly-retreat-since-june.html
China ’s benchmark stock index erased
gains as banks and developers declined, countering an advance by
power producers.  The Shanghai Composite Index was little changed at 2,706.32
at 11:19 a.m., with 474 shares rising and 373 falling. The gauge
has lost 7.1 percent this month, the biggest retreat since June
2010.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
